
=Discussion=

Michel Bauwens:

The increased usage of IT does not showup in productivity statistics, why is that ?

There are three possible reasons:

1) because they have no effect

2) because they have no effect 'yet' (delay)

3) because the effect cannot be measured by the old tools

(source, reading notes from Michel Bauwens, 2004: https://wiki.p2pfoundation.net/Multitudes_2_on_the_New_Political_Economy)

